Subject: CELS Genesis Proposal Process
 

Hello,

 

Below is an update on the CELS-specific process for the Genesis Mission RFA (DE-FOA-0003612). The finance team is ready to assist; however, with 280+ proposals anticipated in CELS, please note that resources are stretched very thin. Providing budget information to your local finance manager as soon as possible is essential.

 

Key Process Notes:

1   Budget Details:
        Please provide budget details to your local finance managers by end of this week, Friday April 10, or sooner, if available
2   ANL-1048 Approvals via SharePoint/BOX:
        Division Directors and PIs will receive email notifications when their review/approval is required on each ANL-1048.
        PI, RPE lead (Steve J.), and Division Director will need to electronically sign and approve each ANL-1048.
            Lead Proposals: ANL-1048s must be signed by EOD April 13. CELS Proposal Team (Lisa C.) will submit to SRO by April 14.
            Partner Proposals: ANL-1048s must be signed by EOD April 20. CELS Proposal Team (Lisa C.) will submit to SRO by April 21. 
3   Grants.gov Workspaces:
        The Finance team will create corresponding workspaces for all approved proposals (Lead and Partner) – please do not create your own.
        Your local division finance manager and the CELS Proposal Team (Lisa C.) will be in contact with specifics for grants.gov for your divisions.
4   CELS Proposal Intake Form CELS Proposal Intake Form :
        We ask all PIs to submit this form for each Genesis application (both Lead and Partner)
        This helps capture key data that will be used in the application.
5   Lead applications:
        CELS Proposal Team (Lisa C.) will coordinate communications with all partners, subrecipients, and ANL key personnel for required proposal items. 
6   Partner applications:
        CELS Proposal Team (Lisa C.) will coordinate communications and submit key documents to the Lead.
        Grants.gov submission is also required for Partner applications. CELS Proposal Team (Lisa C.) will coordinate. 
7   Budget Entry:
        For all proposals (Lead and Partner), please contact your local Finance Manager regarding budget considerations as soon as possible.
        The Finance team will be entering budget information into Grants.gov for all Lead and Partner applications.  

 

Please share this information with your teams. More details will follow as we get updated guidance from SRO. Please let me know if any questions or if the Shared Services team can further assist during this process.

 

Thank you,

 

